function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(w -> isuppercase(w[1]), words)
end
```
This function uses the `filter` method to iterate over the list of words and remove those that do not start with a capital letter. The `isuppercase` function is used to check if the first character of each word is uppercase, which indicates that the word starts with a capital letter.
